radiographic_examinations.findings: The visualized lung bases are clear. No pleural or pericardial effusion. The appendix is dilated to 9-10 mm and fluid-filled with mucosal hyperenhancement. Periappendiceal edema is noted. No rim-enhancing fluid collection is seen adjacent to it. No free air. The small and large bowel are normal in course and caliber without obstruction. No enlarged mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymph nodes are identified. A nonspecific dense focus in the endometrial canal may represent calcification or an enhancing focus. A small amount of free fluid in the pelvis is within the physiologic range or may be reactive. No bone finding suspicious for infection or malignancy is seen.
